
[1]stalking-horse

   STALKING-HORSE, n. A horse, real or factitious, behind which a fowler
   conceals himself from the sight of the game which he is aiming to kill;
   hence, a mask; a pretense.

   Hypocrisy is the devils stalking-horse, under an affectation of
   simplicity and religion.
